"RegExp"

"ObjectRef"
"Reference to a JavaScript object located outside the JSON structure"
"FunctionRef"
"Reference to a JavaScript function."
"JsonProperty"
"Any string or integer that can be used as JSON property - must not be a JavaScript reserved word to avoid potential issues with some browsers"
"name"
"Enum"
"String that can only take a limited number of values - which must be described in the $enumValues Array associated to the element description"
"Object"
"Correspond a structure to with defined parameters : unlike maps, property names are clearly defined. However properties may not be present if not mandatory, and if object is not restricted, other properties might be available. Object description, property name and types must be described in the $properties map of the object schema."
"Array"
"Correspond to variable-length structure where items are indexed with an integer (first = 0). An array contains items of the same type (which can be a MultiTypes), which is described in the $contentType object of the schema description."
"Map"
"Like Arrays, Maps correspond to variable-length structure - but contrary to Arrays, Map items are indexed with strings. A map contains items of the same type (which can be a MultiTypes), which is described in the $contentType object of the schema description."
"MultiTypes"
"A multi type element is an element that can reference items of different types. As such, its possible types should be described in the $contentTypes array of the schema description."
"PackageName"
"String"
"A string which contains a complete path to a package or a class."
